{"color":"RED","isTrashed":false,"isPinned":true,"isArchived":false,"textContent":"Before responding to your wife or kids, ask two questions:\n\n1. What do they need right now?\n2. What do I need right now to stay grounded and honest?\n\nAct only when both answers are clear.\n\n---\n\n5-PART SERVANT LEADER COMMUNICATION LOOP:\n\n1. Seeing \u2013 \u201cI\u2019m noticing\u2026\u201d\n2. Understanding \u2013 \u201cIt makes sense you\u2019d feel that way\u2026\u201d\n3. Needs \u2013 \u201cHere\u2019s what I need right now\u2026\u201d\n4. Support \u2013 \u201cHere\u2019s how I can help you\u2026\u201d\n5. Agreement \u2013 \u201cLet\u2019s find something that works for both of us\u2026\u201d\n\n---\n\nMICRO-BEHAVIORS (DAILY)\n\nWith Wife:\n\n\u201cWhat would support look like today?\u201d\n\n\u201cHere\u2019s where I\u2019m resourced\u2026 here\u2019s where I\u2019m thin.\u201d\n\nReflect emotions before responding.\n\nOffer presence, not solutions.\n\n\nWith 15-Year-Old:\n\nConnect before correcting.\nShare the \u201cwhy\u201d behind decisions.\nGive real choices and power.\nAssign meaningful roles (navigator, planner, photographer).\n\nWith 7-Year-Old:\n\nPredictability + playful connection.\nEye-level listening.\nMicro-missions: \u201cHelp me solve this.\u201d\n\n---\n\nHONEST NEED STATEMENTS (HNS)\n\nTemplate:\n\u201cI\u2019m feeling ___. I need ___. My request is ___.\u201d\n\nExamples:\n\n\u201cI\u2019m feeling overstimulated. I need 5 minutes alone. I\u2019ll come back grounded.\u201d\n\n\u201cI\u2019m feeling disconnected. I need closeness\u2014can we sit together?\u201d\n\n\u201cI\u2019m feeling scattered. I need predictability. Let\u2019s decide a plan first.\u201d\n\n---\n\nFAMILY SERVANT LEADERSHIP AGREEMENTS\n\n1. Speak needs without blame.\n2. Take emotional reality seriously.\n3. Curiosity before correction.\n4. Collaborative decisions for group-impact moments.\n5. Quick repair after conflict.\n \n---\n\nWEEKLY REFLECTION (10 MIN)\n\nWhere did I lead with service?\n\nWhere did I abandon myself?\n\nWhere did I name my needs with courage?\n","title":"SERVE + SELF MODEL","userEditedTimestampUsec":1763661228881000,"createdTimestampUsec":1763660408295000,"textContentHtml":"<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0.0pt;margin-bottom:0.0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size:7.2pt;font-family:'Google Sans';color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;\">Before responding to your wife or kids, ask two questions:<\/span><\/p><br /><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0.0pt;margin-bottom:0.0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size:7.2pt;font-family:'Google Sans';color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;\">1. What do they need right now?<\/span><\/p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0.0pt;margin-bottom:0.0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size:7.2pt;font-family:'Google Sans';color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;\">2. What do I need right now to stay grounded and honest?<\/span><\/p><br /><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0.0pt;margin-bottom:0.0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size:7.2pt;font-family:'Google Sans';color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre;white-space:pre-wrap;\">Act only when both answers are clear.<\/span><\/p><br /><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0.0pt;margin-bottom:0.0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size:7.2pt;font-family:'Google Sans';color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:400;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertic